Section 1:
1 L.D. 1040
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 669, L.D. 1040, “An Act to Raise the
10 Cap on Retirement Benefits for Certain State Employees and Teachers to Which a Cost-
11 of-living Adjustment Is Made”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
13 'Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
14 allocations are made.
15 RETIREMENT SYSTEM, MAINE PUBLIC EMPLOYEES
16 Retirement System - Retirement Allowance Fund 0085
17 Initiative: Provides one-time funds for the actuarial cost of applying the cost-of-living
18 adjustment to the first $40,000 of the retirement benefit being paid to retired state
19 employees and retired teachers who retired on or before June 30, 2011 or their beneficiaries.
20 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
21 All Other $0 $118,240,000
22 __________ __________
23 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $118,240,000
2240 '
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment adds an appropriations and allocations section.
